params.documentation: Filter expression Binary Operators: 'eq', 'ne', 'lt', 'gt', 'le', 'ge', 'mul', 'div', 'mod', 'sub', 'add' Unary Operators: 'not', '-' (minus) String Operators: 'startswith', 'endswith', 'length', 'contains', 'tolower', 'toupper', Nested attributes are composed using '.' Dates must be formatted as yyyy-MM-dd or yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ss[.SSS]Z Strings should enclosed in single quotes, escape single quote with two single quotes The special literal 'created' will be mapped to the time the resource was first created. Examples: - $filter=(updated gt 2016-08-09T13:00:00Z) and (org_id eq 278710ff4e-6b6d-4d4e-aefb-ca637f38609e) - $filter=(created eq 2016-08-09) - $filter=(created gt 2016-08-09) and (sddc.status eq 'READY') (optional)
